article.headline: Army 71, VMI 69
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Senior guard Grant Carter hit a 3-pointer with three seconds left to play to give Army a 71-69 win over VMI on Saturday. A layup by Army's Jarell Brown with 1:17 remaining in the game tied the score at 68, but Reggie Williams hit a free throw with 1:08 on the clock to put VMI ahead by one. Carter's only shot of the game came just over a minute later, clinching the win for the Black Knights (3-4). Williams led the Keydets (3-4) in scoring with 21 points, and Chavis Holmes added 17. Brown led Army with 34 points and 10 rebounds and hit 8 of 9 shots from 3-point range while going 11-of-13 from the floor. Army outshot VMI 58.7 percent to 36.2 percent.
